John H. WALKER, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 11973. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit Dec. 15, 1947. William C. Rayburn, of Guntersville, Ala., for appellant. John D. Hill, U. S. Atty., of Birmingham, Ala., for appellee.

Before McCORD, WALLER, and LEE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

This appeal not having been perfected within the time required, and in accordance with the order of this court on October 21, 1947, it is the opinion of the court that the same be, and it is hereby, dismissed.
